title: Timi Pari | Lekaki Hey Maya - Kandara | Emperor Kripa Unplugged | Season 3
description:
Since its inception back in 2013 Kripa Drishya Digital has been providing this platform KRIPA UNPLUGGED as a means of showcasing popular Nepali musical talents and their music in a stripped down version bringing to you the raw sounds of acoustic music

This time Kripa Unplugged is back with Season 3 joining hands with our Sponsor Emperor Whiskey

In this episode we have the folk rock band from Pokhara coming together after a long hiatus performing their hit singles Timi Pari released in in 1995 and Lekaki Hey Maya released in 1996. Vocalist Bivek Shrestha flew down from Australia to reunite with his band Kandara just for this special performance for their fans on Kripa Unplugged 

Sponsor:  Emperor Whiskey

Song: Timi Pari / Lekaki Hey Maya 
Band: Kandara
Lyricist: Sunil Thapa
Music: Sunil Thapa 
Album: Danda Pari

Kandara are:
Vocals: Bivek Shrestha

title: Highlander Ghar Ma Sessions: Sapana ko Mayalu | The Elements
description:
Highlander Ghar Ma Sessions is an intimate one on one session with bands | artists and fans. 

Bands and artists perform in front of their biggest fans chosen from social media campaigns (click on our Facebook | Instagram links below to know more) at different venues and a lucky few are sent VIP Invitations to attend this private and intimate session and see their favorite artists / bands perform some of their biggest hits while interacting with them one and one,  sipping on some amazing cocktails courtesy Highlander Vodka. 

The Elements are:
Dipesh Gurung - Percussionist 
Raunaq Singh Adhikari - Guitar / Vocals
Ishan R. Onta - Vocals / Guitar 
 
All performances are filmed and recorded live from the venue  

Sponsor: Highlander Pure White Vodka

Sound - Little Star Records
Sound Engineer - Ukesh Pariyar
Mix/ Master - Bizu Karmacharya 
Camera - Rakshak Bhushan Bajracharya / Amar Chitrakar / Anup Adhikari
Edit - Rakshak Bhushan Bajracharya 
Color - Rakshak Bhushan Bajracharya 
Production Manager - Sanat Sharma
Director - Pavel Udas

Ghar Ma Sessions concept - Yanik Shrestha/ Reshma Limbu

Executive Producer: Asish Syangden

Thank you to all the Fans !!

title: Prayas - Samriddhi Rai X Rohit John Chettri | Emperor Kripa Unplugged | Season 3
description:
Since its inception back in 2013 Kripa Drishya Digital has been providing this platform KRIPA UNPLUGGED as a means of showcasing popular Nepali musical talents and their music in a stripped down version bringing to you the raw sounds of acoustic music

This time Kripa Unplugged is back with Season 3 joining hands with our Sponsor Emperor Whiskey

In this Episode we bring to you a song written by Samriddhi Rai after her friends kept on nagging her that she should come out with a love song as at that point she was only writing patriotic and motivational songs. And thus PRAYAS was born and released originally in 2015 as a duet with the talented Rohit John Chettri 

Sponsor:  Emperor Whiskey

description:
Since its inception back in 2013 Kripa Drishya Digital has been providing this platform KRIPA UNPLUGGED as a means of showcasing popular musical talents of the Nepali music industry and their music in a stripped down version bringing to you the raw sounds of acoustic music.

This time Kripa Unplugged is back with Season 3 joining hands with our Sponsor Emperor Whiskey.

On this Third Episode we bring to you the song â€˜NAMUNAâ€™ written by Sabin Rai for his daughter which is from his 2003 Album Sataha 1.

title: Sangi - Shiva Pariyar | Emperor Kripa Unplugged | Season 3
description:
Since its inception back in 2013 Kripa Drishya Digital has been providing this platform KRIPA UNPLUGGED as a means of showcasing popular Nepali musical talents and their music in a stripped down version bringing to you the raw sounds of acoustic music.

This time Kripa Unplugged is back with Season 3 joining hands with our Sponsor Emperor Whiskey.

On this first episode we bring to you SHIVA PARIYAR performing SANGI from the sound track to the movie Batch no.16 released in 2011.
